President Obama has nominated Judge Michael A. Shipp to serve on the United States District Court for the District of New Jersey. Judge Shipp has a long and distinguished record of service, having served as a United States Magistrate Judge in the District of New Jersey since 2007. Prior to his appointment to the bench, he worked in the New Jersey Office of the Attorney General and as an associate at Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher & Flom LLP. Judge Shipp received his J.D. from Seton Hall University School of Law and his B.S. from Rutgers University. President Obama believes that Judge Shipp will serve on the federal bench with distinction.